cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper presents a method for monocular 3D object detection using neural networks and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics and machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes novel loss functions to optimize the neural network, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
